The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) in Kaduna on Sunday declared Alhaji Haruna Inuwa of All Progressives Congress (APC) winner for Gabasawa/Doka State Constituency in Kaduna North Local Government in the March 9 Governorship/State House of Assembly polls. INEC’s Returning Officer in Kaduna North Local Government, Dr Abdulsalam Dalhatu, said Inuwa polled 33,117 votes to defeat his closest contestant of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Alhaji Mohammed Jibrin, who scored 15,990 votes. Dalhatu said “Haruna M. A. Inuwa of the APC, haven satisfied the requirements of the law and scored the highest votes, is hereby declared winner of the Gabasawa/Doka State Constituency.” Also, Prof. Haladu Isa Bayero, the INEC Returning Officer for Kudan Local Government Area, announced Alhaji Faisal Abbas Likoro of the APC as winner of Kudan State Constituency in the Governorship and State Assembly poll in Kaduna State. Bayero said Likoro scored 29,395 votes to defeat Alhaji Junaidu Yakubu of PDP, who scored 20,584 votes. Kudan is the Local government area of Alhaji Isah Ashiru, the Governorship Candidate of the PDP in the state. INEC also declared the PDP as winner of the Chikun State Constituency in the state Assembly election. The Returning Officer, Dr A.Ibrahim, said Mr Uba Kato of the PDP scored 32,186 votes to defeat Mr Peter Turaki of APC who scored 12,202 votes. Meanwhile, INEC has declared Alhaji Isah Ashiru, the governorship candidate of the PDP as winner of the March 9 governorship election in Kajuru Local Government Area of Kaduna State. INEC’s Collation Officer of the local government, Dr A.Ibrahim, who announced the result in Kajuru on Sunday, said Ashiru polled 34,658 votes to defeat Gov. Nasiru El-Rufa’i of APC who got 10,202 votes.(NAN) PDP’s Ashiru loses LG in state assembly election APC, PDP run tight race in Kano, Kaduna, Lagos, Sokoto APC wins Soba federal constituency in Kaduna